ese palettes to customize existing themes or create entirely new ones with confidence. Hover a swatch to see its OKLCH value, and click to copy it."},"34":{"id":"/docs/customize/colors-32","page_id":"/docs/customize/colors","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/customize/colors#default-color-palette-reference","content":"Here's a complete list of the default colors and their values for reference:"},"35":{"id":"/docs/customize/component","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","type":"page","content":"Component Customization","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Customize"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/customize/component"},"36":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-0","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/customize/component","content":"Hummingbird React components can be customized using props, utility classes, or CSS variables to match specific design needs."},"37":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-1","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/customize/component#using-props","content":"Using props"},"38":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-2","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/customize/component#using-tailwind-utility-classes","content":"Using Tailwind utility classes"},"39":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-3","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/customize/component#using-the-apply-directive","content":"Using the `@apply` directive"},"40":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-4","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/customize/component#using-css-variables","content":"Using CSS variables"},"41":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-5","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/customize/component#option-1-global-variables","content":"Option 1: Global variables"},"42":{"id":"/docs/customize/component-6","page_id":"/docs/customize/component","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/doc