-started/installation-10","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#3-import-css","content":"Import Hummingbird styles in the main CSS file (e.g., `globals.css`), and register the package as a source so the Tailwind compiler scans it for class names."},"355":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-11","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#3-import-css","content":"The `@source` directive is required because Tailwind does not scan node\\_modules by default. Since Hummingbird generates component classes on demand, Tailwind must scan the `@hummingbirdui/react` package. Update the relative path so it points to node\\_modules from your CSS file."},"356":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-12","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#3-import-css","content":"No per-component CSS imports or manual purge configuration are needed."},"357":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-13","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#4-use-components","content":"Import any component and use it in the application."},"358":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-14","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#typescript-support","content":"Hummingbird React is written in TypeScript and includes type definitions for all components. Component props are fully typed and available on each component's namespace, so no additional `@types` packages are needed."},"359":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-15","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#customization","content":"All components accept a `className` prop. Custom classes are merged with the component classes, so Tailwind utility classes can be used to adjust any component."},"360":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-16","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#customization","content":"For theme-level changes such as colors and spacing, Hummingbird provides global and component-specific CSS variables. See the Customize section for details."},"361":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","type":"page","content":"Introduction","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Getting Started"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction"},"362":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-0","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","content":"Welcome to the Hummingbird React documentation. It is an open-source React component library built on Hummingbird CSS and Radix UI primitives."},"363":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-1","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#what-is-hummingbird-react","content":"What is Hummingbird React?"},"364":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-2","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#why-hummingbird-react","content":"Why Hummingbird React?"},"365":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-3","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#pre-requisite-knowledge","content":"Pre-requisite knowledge"},"366":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-4","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#join-our-community","content":"Join our community"},"367":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-5","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#what-is-hummingbird-react","content":"Hummingbird React is the official React component library for the Hummingbird design system. It provides a large set of accessible, fully styled React components such as buttons, forms, dialogs, and dropdowns, along with patterns suitable for dashboards, SaaS applications, and e-commerce systems."},"368":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-6","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#what-is-hummingbird-react","content":"The library follows one core principle: **Hummingbird CSS owns the visuals, and Radix UI owns the behavior**. Every component is styled with Hummingbird's component classes on top of Tailwind CSS, while interactive components use Radix UI primitives for keyboard navigation, focus management, and accessibility. Hummingbird React is the bridge between the two."},"369":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-7","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#why-hummingbird-react","content":"Provides ready-to-use React components with a consistent, typed API."},"370":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-8","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#why-hummingbird-react","content":"Ships accessible behavior out of the box through Radix UI primitives."},"371":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-9","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#why-hummingbird-react","content":"Reduces reliance on large sets of Tailwind utility classes."},"372":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-10","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#why-hummingbird-react","content":"Offers component variants through simple props such as `variant`, `color`, and `size`."},"373":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-11","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#why-hummingbird-react","content":"Supports full customization using the `className` prop and Tailwind utility classes."},"374":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-12","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#why-hummingbird-react","content":"Provides global and component-specific CSS variables for deeper configuration."},"375":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-13","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#why-hummingbird-react","content":"Includes complete TypeScript definitions for every component."},"376":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-14","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#why-hummingbird-react","content":"Supports tree shaking through per-component imports."},"377":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-15","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#pre-requisite-knowledge","content":"HTML"},"378":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-16","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#pre-requisite-knowledge","content":"CSS"},"379":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-17","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#pre-requisite-knowledge","content":"JavaScript"},"380":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-18","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#pre-requisite-knowledge","content":"React"},"381":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-19","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#pre-requisite-knowledge","content":"Tailwind CSS"},"382":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction-20","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/introduction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/introduction#join-our-community","content":"If you have any questions about Hummingbird React, you can reach out to our community on GitHub Discussions, Discord or X (Twitter)."},"383":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","type":"page","content":"Grid","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Layout & Content"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/layout/grid"},"384":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-0","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid","content":"The Grid is a twelve-column, flexbox-based layout system built from Container, Row, and Col components. It provides a familiar row and column structure for building responsive designs."},"385":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-1","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/layout/grid#basic-example","content":"Basic example"},"386":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-2","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/layout/grid#auto-layout-columns","content":"Auto-layout columns"},"387":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-3","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/layout/grid#equal-width","content":"Equal-width"},"388":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-4","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/layout/grid#variable-width-content","content":"Variable width content"},"389":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-5","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/layout/grid#responsive-props","content":"Responsive props"},"390":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-6","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/layout/grid#all-breakpoints","content":"All breakpoints"},"391":{"id":"/docs/layo